Patch Set 2:

I ported these patches to the upstream client and tested there. Since I only had mlx4 based hardware in my test environment I change fpo_is_fmr to 1 to force the use of FMR with the mlx4 driver. That is when I saw these errors. The code causing this problem is:

                if (frd) {
                        if (!frd->frd_valid) {
                                wrq = &frd->frd_inv_wr;
                                wrq->next = &frd->frd_fastreg_wr.wr;
                        } else {
                                wrq = &frd->frd_fastreg_wr.wr;
                        }
                        frd->frd_fastreg_wr.wr.next = &tx->tx_wrq[0].wr;
                }

Patch Set 3:

Hi James,
                if (frd) {
                        if (!frd->frd_valid) {
                                wrq = &frd->frd_inv_wr;
                                wrq->next = &frd->frd_fastreg_wr.wr;
                        } else {
                                wrq = &frd->frd_fastreg_wr.wr;
                        }
                        frd->frd_fastreg_wr.wr.next = &tx->tx_wrq[0].wr;
                }
Correct me if am wrong but the code path is for FastReg, If you are using mlx4 and forcing fpo_is_fmr to 1 then you are using FMR, not FastReg, and you should not run into the code above.
